        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 8:09PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 808 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Tuttle, or 41
miles south of Harvey, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tuttle and Robinson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
